			<p>Your game window is probably divided into three sections right now.  On the left you’ll see your dwarfs and the wagon and the immediate area, probably some trees and rocks, maybe a stream.  In the middle is a list of commands, and on the right is a map of the entire embark area.  TAB will cycle through several combinations of these, eventually you’ll probably want to just keep 2/3rd of the screen on the left side as your live action window, and the remaining 3rd on the right as your commands.  Right now though, just take a look around:</p>
			<p><strong>The "k" key will describe the item(s) directly beneath your cursor.</strong> This is both inside and outside your fort.</p>
			<p><strong>East, West, North, and South movement</strong> is done with the arrow keys.</p>
			<p><strong>Moving UP and DOWN Z levels</strong> is done with < and >.  You’ll get very familiar with all these basic navigations.</p>
			
