		<div id="cont_right">
			<p>If you get lost, <strong>F1</strong> will zoom you to your wagon.</p>
			<p><a href="images/tut_img/gamewindow2.jpg"><img width="100%" src="images/tut_img/gamewindow2.jpg"/></a></p>
			<p>Notice that if you go down one Z level while you’re looking at a river or a brook, you will see the actual river and the sides of it even one level down.</p>
			<p>Keep this in mind; you don’t want to mine into a river by accident and your dwarves will CANCEL any tiles designated for mining if they feel damp stone or soil, forcing you to pause and examine the situation. This can happen even one Z level down from the lowest level of water.</p>
			<p>For example, it might be pretty obvious when you’re mapping out an area to be dug out when you can see the river there at Z -1, but at Z -2 it becomes less intuitive; there are still tiles that are “next to” a water source, it’s just that the water source is ABOVE you.  So you will still get some pausing and canceling of designated mining at Z -2, usually these are safe to mine.</p>
